# Auto push & preview (AgentOS)

The user does **not** want a manual git workflow. Deploy pipeline: **git push → GitHub → Vercel** (Next.js).

## When to commit and push

Do all of the following unless the user says **not** to push:

1. User says **push**, **发布**, **部署**, or similar.
2. You finished a **feature** or meaningful UI change (not tiny typos unless they asked).
3. End of a task where the user should **see the result in the browser**.

Do **not** wait for the user to run `git add` / `git commit` / `git push` themselves.

## Push workflow (agent runs this)

1. `git status` — if nothing to commit, say so and still confirm remote is up to date.
2. Run `npm run build` when the change touches app code; fix failures before pushing.
3. Stage only project files — never `.env`, `.env.local`, credentials, or secrets.
4. Commit with a clear message (feat/fix/chore + what changed).
5. `git push` (or `git push -u origin <branch>` for a new branch).
6. If push fails (auth, network), report the exact error and what the user must run once (usually `gh auth login`).

## After every successful push — reply with links

Always include in your message:

- **GitHub**: commit or branch URL (`https://github.com/pdrdzyk/agentos/...`)
- **View UI**: tell them to open the Vercel deployment
  - `main` → production: `https://agentos.vercel.app` or the project’s Production URL from Vercel dashboard
  - feature branch → Preview URL from the latest Vercel deploy (or GitHub PR Checks if a PR exists)

If Vercel is not connected yet, say so once and point to `DEPLOY.md` — do not make the user guess.

## After every successful push — 代码简报 (for Claude)

The user copies your chat reply **directly into Claude** — they do **not** want to open GitHub to collect code. **Always** append **`## 代码简报`** after push or feature completion.

**Critical:** Put the **actual full source code** in the chat message. GitHub links are supplementary only, never a substitute for pasting files.

Use this structure (keep concise, factual, copy-paste friendly):

```markdown
## 代码简报

**日期**: YYYY-MM-DD
**仓库**: https://github.com/pdrdzyk/agentos
**提交**: <short sha> — <commit title>
**链接**: <commit URL>

### 本轮目标
<1–2 sentences: what the user asked for>

### 已完成
- <bullet: user-visible outcome>
- <bullet: technical change>

### 主要改动文件
- `path/to/file` — <why>
- ...

### 改动文件全文（直接给用户的代码）
**Required:** Paste the **complete, copy-paste-ready source** of every **newly created** or **significantly modified** file in this chat turn. The user will forward this section to Claude as-is.

Do **not** say “见 GitHub” instead of pasting code. Do **not** only list filenames.

Format for each file:

````
#### `path/to/file`
<optional one-line: why changed>

```<language>
<entire file contents>
```
````

Rules:
- **New file** → always include full content.
- **Significantly modified** → include full content of the file as it exists after the change (not a diff-only summary).
- **Trivial edits** (typo, single comment) → list in「主要改动文件」only; omit from「改动文件全文」.
- **Never** paste secrets (`.env`, `.env.local`, keys, tokens) or huge generated artifacts (`package-lock.json`, `.next/**`) unless the user explicitly asks.
- If a file is unreasonably large for one message, include full content up to the practical limit, then note「其余见 commit」and link the commit.

### 未接 / 刻意未做
- <e.g. 未接 Anthropic、群聊仍为 mock>

### 如何查看
- 本地: `npm run dev` → http://localhost:3000
- 线上: <Vercel production or preview URL, or “待连 Vercel”>

### 建议 Claude 下一步
<1–3 bullets aligned with user direction, e.g. 继续装修 UI 而非接 AI>
```

Write in **中文** unless the user used English for that turn. No secrets in the brief.

## Branching (recommended for features)

- Default: push to `main` for small MVP steps.
- For larger features: `feature/<short-name>`, push branch, mention Preview URL; merge to `main` when user confirms.

## Constraints

- Never force-push `main`, never skip hooks unless the user asks.
- Never commit API keys or `.env.local`.
- User saying **only push** means push only — do not add unrelated changes.
